incorporation of units into programming languages.wthe issues of how a programming language mightaid in keeping track of physical units (feet, sec, etc.) are discussed.  a method is given for theintroduction of relationships among units (a watt is volts*amps, a yard is three feet) and subsequent automaticconversion based upon these relationships. various proposals for syntax are considered.cacm may, karr, m.loveman iii, d.b..kunits, language design, compiler construction, language syntax.c. .ca dh february ,   : pm